# Labelo – Decentralized RLHF Protocol on Initia

A full-stack MVP for the hackathon: a two-sided decentralized data-labeling and RLHF marketplace built on an Initia MiniEVM rollup chain, with session-key auto-signing for zero-friction mobile workers and a clean enterprise B2B dashboard.

---

## Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph TD
    A["Enterprise Dashboard\n(labelo.com/enterprise)"] -->|deposit USDC + upload dataset| B["BountyEscrow.sol\n(Initia MiniEVM)"]
    B -->|task queue written| C["Supabase (PostgreSQL)\nTask & Worker DB"]
    D["Worker App\n(labelo.com / mobile)"] -->|connect wallet + autosign session| B
    D -->|fetch task| C
    D -->|submit label| E["Node.js API\n(Express/TypeScript)"]
    E -->|verify + call distributePayment| B
    B -->|0.1 USDC streamed| D
    F["Assets (S3/IPFS)"] -->|image/prompt URLs| C
```

**Key principles:**
- Blockchain = financial settlement + identity only
- Off-chain DB (Supabase) = task routing, progress tracking
- Session keys (InterwovenKit `enableAutoSign`) = frictionless mobile UX
- MiniEVM (Solidity) = hackathon speed, EVM familiarity

---

## Repo Structure

```
labelo/
├── contracts/          # Foundry project – BountyEscrow.sol
├── backend/            # Node.js + Express + TypeScript API
└── frontend/           # Next.js 14 App Router (worker + enterprise)
