## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Do you have a deployed Initia testnet rollup (chain ID) you want to target?**
> The MiniEVM testnet chain is `minievm-2` (chain ID `4303131403034904`). If you have a custom rollup already spun up, share its RPC + chain ID and we'll point the contract + frontend there. Otherwise we'll target the shared Initia MiniEVM testnet.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Smart contract payment token – real USDC or a testnet mock ERC-20?**
> For the hackathon demo we'll deploy a `MockUSDC.sol` (18-decimal ERC-20) so you can mint freely and show the flow. If you have a bridged USDC address on the testnet, we can use that directly.

> [!NOTE]
> **Backend hosting**: The Node.js API and Supabase need to be reachable by the frontend. For the hackathon we can either (a) run the backend locally and demo on localhost, or (b) deploy to Railway/Render for a live URL. We'll design to support both; just let us know your preference.

